<p><img src="https://cdn.blot.im/blog_177bc256f0ee469c998e912e20ece048/_image_cache/13443667-7655-41ff-9cff-330049d1912e.jpg" alt="Ink drawing of a page being shredded. The top of the page is intact, and the words “Focus not on CAN’T” are visible. The bottom of the page is falling away in tiny pieces, and the words “But on” can be seen amongst them. These pieces have fallen into clumps at the bottom, making up the word “CAN”." width="1677" height="1205"></p>
<p><em>Ink on paper, drawn with non-dominant hand</em></p>
<hr>
<p>There will always be things we aren’t able to do, directions we cannot follow. The trick to contentment is to focus on what we <em>can</em> do. No matter how hard things get, there is always at least one positive action before us.</p>
